Feature 3: Agenda & Task Management

This feature helps organize and track agenda points during meetings, assign responsibilities, and monitor task completion.

Epic 3.1: Agenda Point Management

Users must be able to add, update, and manage discussion points.

User Stories:

Add Agenda Points: As a user, I want to add agenda points to a meeting so that meeting discussions are well-structured.

Edit/Delete Agenda Points: As a user, I want to edit or delete agenda points to maintain accurate meeting records.

View Agenda Points: As a user, I want to view all agenda points in a structured list to follow meeting discussions easily.

Epic 3.2: Responsibility Assignment

Each agenda point must have a clear owner.

User Stories:

Assign Responsible Person: As a user, I want to assign a responsible person to each agenda point so that tasks have accountability.

Select from Contacts: As a user, I want to select responsible persons from the team contacts list to save time.

View Responsibility: As a user, I want to see the responsible person next to each agenda point so that accountability is visible.

Epic 3.3: Task Status Tracking

Users need to monitor the completion of agenda points.

User Stories:

Mark Open/Closed: As a user, I want to mark an agenda point as open or closed to track task completion.

Visual Status Indicators: As a user, I want to see visual indicators (like color badges) for open and closed tasks for quick understanding.

Remove Closed Tasks: As a user, I want closed agenda points removed from the active agenda list to reduce clutter.